abstract: Mr. Biden is a different kind of Democrat than most of the other leading contenders: more inclined to bipartisanship and, in some cases, more moderate.
snippet: Mr. Biden is a different kind of Democrat than most of the other leading contenders: more inclined to bipartisanship and, in some cases, more moderate.
lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., who opened his third run for the presidency on Thursday, holds political views that can look and sound similar to the priorities of many liberals, but differ on some key details. Mr. Biden, who has a longer record in politics than any other Democrat in the sprawling 2020 field, will come under close scrutiny for those differences; one liberal group, Justice Democrats, has already come out to oppose him because of “centrist” views.

headline_main: Biden on the Issues: Where He Stands and How He’s Changed

abstract: The former vice president has stayed on the sidelines while his record has been scrutinized. His entry is sure to reshape the Democratic primary contest.
snippet: The former vice president has stayed on the sidelines while his record has been scrutinized. His entry is sure to reshape the Democratic primary contest.
lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. announced Thursday that he would seek the Democratic nomination to challenge President Trump in 2020, casting the election as a national emergency and asking Democrats to put the task of defeating Mr. Trump above all their other ambitions.

abstract: Facebook and the agency have been in negotiations over a financial penalty for claims that the company violated a 2011 consent decree.
snippet: Facebook and the agency have been in negotiations over a financial penalty for claims that the company violated a 2011 consent decree.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Facebook said on Wednesday that it expected to be fined up to $5 billion by the Federal Trade Commission for privacy violations. The penalty would be a record by the agency against a technology company and a sign that the United States was willing to punish big tech companies.

abstract: Eight Democratic presidential candidates took questions on racial, gender and economic justice, addressing a crucial constituency in the primary.
snippet: Eight Democratic presidential candidates took questions on racial, gender and economic justice, addressing a crucial constituency in the primary.
lead_paragraph: Women of color are an increasingly powerful voting bloc and an essential part of any winning Democratic coalition. But presidential candidates rarely speak directly to them.

headline_main: Donald Trump, Sri Lanka, N.B.A.: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: A lot of would-be presidents are clever people. Few have a cleverness so well targeted toward liberal intellectuals.
snippet: A lot of would-be presidents are clever people. Few have a cleverness so well targeted toward liberal intellectuals.
lead_paragraph: Late this March, a Norwegian news outlet sprang a surprise question on Pete Buttigieg, the mayor of South Bend, Ind., and candidate for president. The previous week, the writer Anand Giridharadas, who has close to half a million Twitter followers, tweeted that he met Buttigieg and introduced him to a Norwegian friend. “Instantaneously,” he wrote, “Mayor Pete starts talking to her in Norwegian, like a magic trick.” Apparently Buttigieg had read a Norwegian novel in translation and been so taken by it that he learned the language just to finish the author’s untranslated works.

headline_main: How Pete Buttigieg’s Meaningless Erudition Made Him the ‘Smart’ Candidate

abstract: Noah said that while Elizabeth Warren and Kamala Harris came to the CNN town hall armed with actual policies, Pete Buttigieg apparently tried to wing it.
